2006-10-10 16:37 UTC-0500 Ron Pinkas <ron/at/xharbour.com>
  * xharbour/source/vm/hvm.c
    * Minor consistency cleanup regarding #ifdef __WIN32__ (I hope I'm not missing something)

  * source\rtl\win32ole.prg
  * xharbour/source/vm/hvm.c
    * Moved OleInitialize() and OleUnInitialize() from INIT/EXIT procedures in win32ole.prg into hb_vmInit()/hb_vmQuit()
      /* This solves GPF trap related to TOleAuto DESTRUCTOR called after OleUnInitialize() was already called. */

  * source\rtl\win32ole.prg
    + Added OleAddRef() to increase the counter of an IDispatch interface.
    * Modified New() to call OleAddref() when an IDispatch is passed.
      /* This solved a GPF trap related to our DESTRUCTOR always calling OleReleaseObject() thus not being symetric. */
    * Mofified VT_BOOL conversion logic to check for VARIANT_FALSE rather then VARIANT_TRUE because some servers don't
      follow VARIANT_TRUE convention.
    * Commented a line that was converting type of a BYREF HB_IT_LOGICAL to HB_IT_LONG (later restored) - I don't understand/recall it's origin.

2006-10-09 22:00 UTC+0300 Pavel Tsarenko <tpe2@mail.ru>
  * makefile.wc
  * source/codepage/cphr437.c
    ! fixed 2 typos in my previos commit

2006-10-10 11:07 UTC+0100 Miguel Angel Marchuet <miguelangel@marchuet.net>
   *source/rdd/bmdbfcdx/bmdbfcdx1.c
    ! fixed size of map filter when a pevious scope is set.
   *source/rdd/dbcmd.c
   *source/rdd/workarea.c
    + Added capabilitie of SET OPTIMIZE ON |OFF over filters
      In the RDD that admit optimization, p. ej. BMDBFCDX, SET OPTIMIZE
      it determines if the filters will be optimized using the open order
      formations in the area of present work. If this indicator is activated (ON),
      controller RDD will optimize the search of registries that fulfill the
      condition established by the filter, diminishing the reading of data of
      the file of data base.
      If the indicator is deactivated (OFF), it does not optimize itself.

2006-10-09 22:00 UTC+0300 Pavel Tsarenko <tpe2@mail.ru>
