2006-09-14 23:23 UTC-0800 Brian Hays <bhays at abacuslaw.com>
  * gd\MAKE_B32.BAT
    *  fixed so if you use envvar BCDIR you don't have to also create
       a BCCDIR to be able to build

  * contrib/rdd_ads/ads1.c
    * fixed bug where the Found flag set by AdsSeek() was incorrect.
      This code is activated only when ADS cannot serve a filter itself
      and filtering is done at the app level.  If the first "hit" from a
      seek landed on a bad record, SKIPFILTER would move to the appropriate
      following record but the Found() flag was wrong.
      For those who might want to test carefully, here's my detailed note:


      If a filter is set that is not valid for ADS, we need to skip
      off of any invalid records (IOW, filter at the Harbour level if ADS can't
      because the filter has UDFs or PUBLICVAR references).
      To make sure the skipped-to record still matches the seeked key, we need to
      be able to construct a comparable key for the subsequent record.
      This is annoyingly complex with the various ads key types for various table types.
      AdsExtractKey would seem to be the api of choice, but here on the starting end the
      key we seek on does NOT match the format of what we get back from AdsExtractKey.
      So I'm saving off the first found record's key, and passing that to our
      adsIndexKeyCmp() to compare to the new record's key.
      We're relying on testing to verify that partial key searches and binary
      raw keys all end up working right.

2006-09-14 11:31 UTC-0500 Ron Pinkas <ron/at/xharbour.com>
  * source/vm/classes.c
    + Added prg callable __ClsCntClasses() to return count of defined classes

2006-09-14 11:02 UTC-0500 Ron Pinkas <ron/at/xharbour.com>
  * source/vm/hvm.c
    * Restored HASH support in HB_P_IVARREF (used in array assignment syntax hHash["Key"] := Value
    + Added overloading support to  HB_P_IVARREF

