2006-09-06 18:30 UTC+0300 Mindaugas Kavaliauskas <dbtopas /at/ dbtopas . lt>
  * source/compiler/harbour.c
    ! Fixed .hil creation. Compiler GPFed on code: i18n("%s%s%s%s")
      The same fix allows to use formatting for string internationalization,
      ex. sprintf(i18n("Count: %d"), nCount)
  * source/vm/hbi18n.c
    + Implemented placement of I18N tables into .exe resource (for Win32).
      To include I18N tables into resource just it add to your project .rc file:
         en_UK     I18N    en_UK.hit
         lt_LT     I18N    lt_LT.hit
         ...
      Languages tables will be linked into .exe file and separate .hit files
      will not be required. If language table is available in both resource
      and external .hit file, HB_I18NSETLANGUAGE gives priority to .hit file.

