2006-08-19 13:40 UTC-0300 Eduardo Fernandes <modalsist@yahoo.com.br>
  * source\rtl\memoedit.prg
    + added K_SH_LEFT and K_SH_RIGHT in aExtKeys data to allow select
      text at shift-right/shift-left keys.
    - removed nLineLength argument treatment, transferred to HbEditor.

  * source\rtl\teditor.prg
    ! changed New() method to fix nLineLenght treatment in compliance with
      Clipper. If nLineLengh is nil, lwordwrap will be true and nWordWrapCol
      will be nRight-nLeft+1. If nLineLenght is < 0, nLineLenght will be 255
      and lWordWrap will be .f., otherwise nLineLenght will be Max(6,nLineLength).
    + added text selection at shift-right and shift-left keys.
    * changed nSelStart data to nRowSelStart, nSelEnd data to nRowSelEnd.
    + added new nColSelStart and nColSelEnd datas.
    + added nTextRow, nTextCol, nWndRow and nWndCol datas to future use.
    * changed SetTextSelection() method to work properly wih shift-down,
      shift-up, shift-right and shif-left keys if HB_EXT_INKEY define is used.
    * changed to call Clttextselection() method if any movement/edit key is
      typed by keyboard or mouse.
    * reverted Ctrl-A behaviour. This always will select all text.
      To unselect all, press any movement or edit key.

