2006-08-13 22:55 UTC-0300 Eduardo Fernandes <modalsist@yahoo.com.br>
  * source\rtl\teditor.prg
    * fixed K_Bs() method (backspace) to repos the cursor at end of previous
      line. Bug reported by Ed Horbino.

    * changes for HB_EXT_INKEY use only:

    ! fixed to exit and save with K_ALT_W if HB_EXT_INKEY is declared.
    * changed: method K_Del() now has double function, if HB_EXT_INKEY is declared
      and text selection is active, delete selected text, otherwise delete
      char as usual.
    * changed SetTexSelection() method to select and unselect text in any
      direction ( shift-down/up and up/down).
    * fixed the GetTextSelection() method to return only selected lines.
    * fixed the AddText() method to insert lines accordly. This was inserting
      an empty line before and after of the selected text.
    * changed Ctrl-C to maintain selected text after copy.
    * changed Ctrl-A (select all) to toggle between select/unselect all text
      after first type.
    * fixed Edit() method to call ::ClrTextSelection() after any movement or
      edition key.

     NOTE: if you build xHarbour with -DHB_EXT_INKEY flag, you must declare
     #define HB_EXT_INKEY in your main prg to avoid unexpected results,
     at same way, if you build xHarbour without -DHB_EXT_INKEY, you must
     disable #define HB_EXT_INKEY in your main prg.

  * source\rtl\memoedit.prg
    - removed aUnhandledKeys DATA.
    + added aExtKeys DATA for use with HB_EXT_INKEY only.
    * review to manage return keys code from udf with and without the use of
      HB_EXT_INKEY constant.

