2006-07-17 14:55 UTC+0200 Przemyslaw Czerpak (druzus/at/priv.onet.pl)
  - xharbour/source/rtl/dbdelim_old.prg
    - deleted

  * xharbour/source/rdd/Makefile
  * xharbour/source/rtl/Makefile
  - xharbour/source/rtl/dbdelim.prg
  - xharbour/source/rtl/dbjoin.prg
  - xharbour/source/rtl/dbsdf.prg
  + xharbour/source/rdd/dbdelim.prg
  + xharbour/source/rdd/dbjoin.prg
  + xharbour/source/rdd/dbsdf.prg
    * moved RDD related .prg files from rtl to rdd directory (library)
      Non GNU make files must be updated. I'd like to ask Marek or
      other Windows developers to borrow non GNU make files from Harbour
      to xHarbour. Now in Harbour there is only one list with dependences
      common.mak which is common for all other make systems and header
      files designed for given makes (currently two: makefile.bc, makefile.vc)
      They can create static build and DLLs. For changing file location,
      adding new ones or deleting some existing files needs only one file
      to be updated - one entry for each file. I'd like to see the same in
      xHarbour and only more header files if we want to support more non
      GNU make systems.

  * xharbour/source/rdd/dbcmd.c
  * xharbour/source/rdd/dbfuncs.prg
  * xharbour/source/rdd/dblist.prg
  * xharbour/source/rdd/dbsort.prg
  * xharbour/source/rdd/dbstrux.prg
  * xharbour/source/rdd/dbtotal.prg
  * xharbour/source/rdd/dbupdat.prg
  * xharbour/source/rdd/rddord.prg
  * xharbour/source/rdd/dbdelim.prg
  * xharbour/source/rdd/dbjoin.prg
  * xharbour/source/rdd/dbsdf.prg
    * updated Victor's fixes from Harbour, here is his ChangeLog entry:

     % Cleanups, minor optimizations.
     ! __dbApp(), __dbCopy() to return LOGICAL.
     ! Problem where error condition was not detected if BREAK didn't
       set the error object.
     ! __dbTotal() lRest handling fixed.
     ! __dbTotal() ErrorBlock overriding removed.
     ! __dbCreate() now generating default alias.
     % __dbCreate() using dbCreate() undoc param to open the tables.
     ! __dbDelim() return value.
     ! __dbSDF() return value.
     + CA-Cl*pper undocumented call added: _dtxCondSet()
     + XBase++ compatible calls implemented:
       dbJoin(), dbList(), dbSort(), dbTotal(), dbUpdate(), _dbExport()
       dbCopyStruct(), dbCopyExtStruct()
     + Added some more 10 chars call stubs:
       __dbCopySt(), __dbCopyXS(), __dbOpenSD(), __dbArrang()
     + Comments.
     + Formatting.
     ; All high-level db functions seems to be compatible now.

     Ron this is sth what I've not synced yet. Seems that Victor is right
     and the translation is (should be) done by compiler not internally by
     __dbList() function so we can safely remove HB_aExpressions() calls.
        - Removed compiler+RTL __dbList() hack which
          made it incompatible with CA-Cl*pper. The
          hack targeted an XBase++ extension, but it's
          compatible even without the hack. Tested with
          XBase++ 1.82.294.
     Can you confirm?

