2006-07-16 21:46 UTC+0200 Przemyslaw Czerpak (druzus/at/priv.onet.pl)
  * xharbour/config/dos/watcom.cf
  * xharbour/config/linux/gcc.cf
  * xharbour/config/w32/mingw32.cf
  * xharbour/config/w32/watcom.cf
  * xharbour/source/rtl/gtgui/Makefile
  * xharbour/source/rtl/gtgui/gtdef.c
  * xharbour/source/rtl/gtnul/Makefile
  * xharbour/source/rtl/gtnul/gtsys.c
  * xharbour/source/rtl/gtnul/gtnul.c
    * changed HB_DEFAULT_GT to HB_GT_DEFAULT

  * xharbour/include/hbapigt.h
  * xharbour/source/rtl/gtnul/gtnul.c
    * added support setting default GT driver by REQUEST HB_GT_<name>_DEFAULT
      Now you useer can add to their source code:
         REQUEST HB_GT_WIN
         REQUEST HB_GT_WVT_DEFAULT
         REQUEST HB_GT_STD
         REQUEST HB_GT_GUI
      to force linking four GT drivers and setting WVT as default one in
      MULTI GT builds.
      If code is linked dynamically with harbour.dll which contain all GT
      drivers then to set the default one it's enough to add to .prg code:
         REQUEST HB_GT_<name>_DEFAULT
      F.e.
         REQUEST HB_GT_GUI_DEFAULT

  * xharbour/source/rtl/gtQTc/mouseQTc.c
  * xharbour/source/rtl/gt_tpl/gt_tpl.c
  * xharbour/source/rtl/gtcgi/gtcgi.c
