      hb_gtSetDefault( "GUI" ) at startup

2006-06-27 23:25 UTC+0200 Przemyslaw Czerpak (druzus/at/priv.onet.pl)
  * xharbour/include/hbrddcdx.h
  * xharbour/include/hbrdddbf.h
  * xharbour/include/hbrdddbt.h
  * xharbour/include/hbrddfpt.h
  * xharbour/include/hbrddntx.h
  * xharbour/source/rdd/dbf1.c
  * xharbour/source/rdd/dbfcdx/dbfcdx1.c
  * xharbour/source/rdd/dbfdbt/dbfdbt1.c
  * xharbour/source/rdd/dbffpt/dbffpt1.c
  * xharbour/source/rdd/dbfntx/dbfntx1.c
    * removed SYSNAME() method - use the default WA one.

  * xharbour/source/vm/hvm.c
    ! fixed HB_P_MACROPUSHINDEX
      - fixed GPF in direct uninitialized HB_ITEM assignment
      - fixed memory leak
      There is a set of global hb_vm*Extra* variables which
      tries to extend HVM by adding some additional registers
      to it. This code does not work as it should even now
      and it's absolutely not reentrant safe. It will have to
      be fixed because it may cause GPF in .prg destructor.

2006-06-27 13:50 UTC-0400 Gerald Drouillard <gerald@drouillard.ca>
